  "metaTitle": "Severance and Releases: What a Defensible Agreement Needs &mdash; Tom Cedoz",
  "metaDescription": "A checklist for building a severance agreement and release that actually holds up: consideration, scope, OWBPA for employees 40+, NLRB limits on confidentiality and non-disparagement, and the practical terms.",
  "standfirst": "A release you paid for is worth nothing if it doesn&rsquo;t bar the claim you were buying peace from. Most defective releases fail in predictable places &mdash; thin consideration, an overbroad scope, a missed age-waiver formality, or a confidentiality clause that now draws its own charge. This checklist walks the agreement in the order a court will read it.",
  "docMetaItems": [
